A 27-year-old man will appear at the Hlanganani Magistrate Court on Thursday after he was arrested for illegally selling medication. According to Hawks in Limpopo, the man was arrested during a raid at an outlet in Elim during a joint operation between the Department of Health inspectors and Hawks. Hawks spokesperson Matimba Maluleke said a lot of medicinal products were found during the operation. “We found an assortment of medical products which included, ointments, creams and tablets valued at approximately R120 000. “The suspect charges relating to contravening Sec 22A of Medicines Act 101 of 1965 as amended and Control of Medicines and Scheduled Substance, Medical Devices,” he said. -TNA Reporter  